From: skinny-l <azizdj2002@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 20:50:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Apple-coded UI redesign
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CSS-only + minor markup pass, every existing class name and CSS
variable (--bg,--p,--p2,--ln,--ink,--mt,--ac,--ok,--wn,--er,--br,--kb)
kept identical so no JS/HTML logic changes needed.

- Palette: real macOS dark system surfaces (#1c1c1e/#2c2c2e/#3a3a3c)
  and system colors (systemBlue/Green/Orange/Red/Purple).
- Tabs: segmented-control pill bar replacing the underline tab strip
  — the one signature element, everything else stays quiet.
- Header: sticky, translucent, backdrop-blurred toolbar.
- Cards: continuous-style 16px radius, hairline borders instead of
  hard 1px lines.
- Buttons: capsule/pill shape, press + hover states, focus-visible
  ring.
- Inputs: filled fields, blue focus ring (accessible keyboard focus).
- Toast: frosted HUD-style with a colored accent bar instead of a
  full colored ring.
- Modal overlay: added backdrop blur.
- Added a max-640px breakpoint collapsing .r2/.r3 grids to a single
  column — pre-existing gap, not a regression, fixed while in here.
- prefers-reduced-motion respected.
- Verified via Playwright screenshots: all 6 tabs, full parse-results
  flow (badges/KB matches/similar cases/report), and mobile width.
  All 25 existing tests still pass (pure front-end change, no
  backend touched).
